calculate_threshold_increase.browser_title = Calculate the residence nil rate band (RNRB) for the estate of someone who has died
calculate_threshold_increase.title = Calculate the residence nil rate band (RNRB) for the estate of someone who has died
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance1 = If there is any RNRB available, this will be added to the Inheritance Tax threshold and might mean there is less tax to pay.
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance2 = This service will calculate how much allowance is available to add to the threshold. It should take you no more than 30 minutes to complete the service.
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance3 = You’ll need to:
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance3.bullet1 = fill in an IHT-435 form to claim the allowance on an estate and you’ll be given a copy after using the service with the details you have given already added
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance3.bullet2 = have a copy of the IHT-400 form that you have been filling in as details will be needed to help work out the available allowance
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance3.bullet3 = have details of any properties owned by the person who has died, including the values of the property and of any debts owed against it
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance3.bullet4 = know who was left property from the estate if it was passed in a will
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance4 = The RNRB allowance can be increased if the person who has died had downsized their home before their death, or if they had been married during their lifetime and their spouse or civil partner died first. To claim any extra allowance you’ll need to have:
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance4.bullet1 = details of the home sold by the person who died
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance4.bullet2 = details of any other assets left in the will to a direct descendant, including the value of these assets
calculate_threshold_increase.guidance4.bullet3 = a completed IHT-436 form with the value of transferable residential nil rate band being claimed if the person who has died was married during their lifetime and their spouse or civil partner died first
calculate_threshold_increase.sub_heading = Before you start

